snippet: In parts of England, the wettest January on record has left whole villages flooded and residents cut off from vital services. And it is still raining.
abstract: Muchelney Journal; Muchelney, England, and adjacent hamlet of Thorney are among areas hardest hit by wettest January on record; copious rains have left whole villages flooded and residents cut off from vital services.
lead_paragraph: In parts of England, the wettest January on record has left whole villages flooded and residents cut off from vital services. And it is still raining.

headline.print_headline: Accustomed to Floods, ‘But Nothing Like This,’ in Southern England
headline.main: Accustomed to Floods, but ‘Nothing Like This,’ in Southern England
